T1  - A Systems Theory of Organizational Conflict
AU  - Pondy, Louis R.
Y1  - 1966/09/01
PY  - 1966
DA  - 1966/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255122
DO  - 10.5465/255122
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 246
EP  - 256
VL  - 9
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Four ?subsystems? of activity within an organization are identified?informational, political, functional, and social. Conflict among the subunits of an organization may occur within any one of these subsystems. Informational conflict, in particular, is due to goal differences among interdependent subunits. But informational conflict affects and is affected by conflict occurring in the other three subsystems as well.
