N2  - The article discusses issues concerning the theories of organization. There has been confusion regarding the definition of organizational theory in relation to organizational behavior. In practice, organization cannot be isolated from objectives, technology, resources, operations, behavior and environment. Developing theories of organizations involves the search for relevant variables and boundaries that are associated with organizational management.
